# Awesome Skills Installation Plan

## Goal Description
Install all 243+ skills from `sickn33/antigravity-awesome-skills` into `.agent/skills/`, but renamed using a "Deep Namespace" strategy (e.g., `growth-seo-audit`) to emulate folder organization within Antigravity's flat structure requirements.

## Proposed Changes
I will use a Python script to automate this decision-making and copying process.

### Category Mapping Logic
The script will detect keywords in the skill name to assign prefixes:

| Keyword | Prefix |
| :--- | :--- |
| `seo`, `keyword` | `growth-seo-` |
| `social`, `linkedin`, `twitter` | `growth-social-` |
| `copy`, `email`, `blog` | `growth-content-` |
| `metasploit`, `hack`, `exploit`, `pentest` | `sec-redteam-` |
| `owasp`, `xss`, `injection` | `sec-psirt-` |
| `react`, `frontend`, `css` | `dev-frontend-` |
| `docker`, `aws`, `azure`, `terraform` | `dev-ops-` |
| `loki`, `autonomous`, `agent` | `auto-agent-` |
| *(Default for others)* | `general-` |

### Execution
1.  Run `scripts/install_skills.py` (which I will create).
2.  The script reads `temp_awesome_skills/skills/`.
3.  It copies each folder to `.agent/skills/` with the new name.
4.  It updates the `name:` field in `SKILL.md` to match the new folder name (critical for Antigravity compatibility).

## Verification
- List `.agent/skills` to confirm the new sorting.
- Test one renamed skill (`growth-seo-audit`) to ensure it loads.
